{
  "_id": "qK86ENPT9V2BiYWT",
  "name": "Divine Retribution",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/items/inventory/badge-cross.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As a standard action, you can point at one creature within 30 feet to indicate that it is the target of divine wrath. A mishap or an accident appropriate to the environment occurs, such as a branch falling on the creature, rocks falling from the ceiling, or some other nonmagical misfortune; regardless of the cause, the mishap deals 1d6 points of damage + 1 point for every two inquisitor levels you possess (Reflex half). The GM decides whether this damage is bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage. You can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 + your Wisdom modifier.</p>"
    },
